\begin_layout Subsection*
\noindent
Question 1.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
The recursive problem is
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\upsilon(s_{t},\,a_{t})=\underset{\underline{a}\leq a_{t+1}\leq\frac{y(s_{t})+a_{t}}{q_{t}}}{max}\left\{ \frac{(y(s_{t})+a_{t}-a_{t+1}q_{t})^{1-\sigma}}{1-\sigma}+\beta\mathbb{E}_{s_{t+1}|s_{t}}[\upsilon(s_{t+1},\,a_{t+1})]\right\} 
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
where 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{t},\,a_{t}$
\end_inset

 are state variables and 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{t+1}$
\end_inset

 is the control variable.
 State space 
\begin_inset Formula $s=\{employed\,(e),\,unemployed\,(u)\}$
\end_inset

.
 Note that 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{t+1}\in[\underline{a},\,\frac{y(s_{t})+a_{t}}{q_{t}}]$
\end_inset

.
 With the budget constraint 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{t}=y(s_{t})+a_{t}-a_{t+1}q_{t}$
\end_inset

, the conditions of market clearence must be fulfilled.
 i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum C(s)=\sum y(s)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum a(s)=0$
\end_inset


\end_layout

